16/04/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- With the help of European colleagues, Bulgarian police broke up a ring smuggling cars from Western Europe to Bulgaria.
National Police Director Gen Vassil Vassilev said Tuesday (15 April) that the operation, dubbed "Adriatica", involved the police forces of Spain, Belgium and Switzerland.
The ring managed to smuggle 80-90 cars from Spain, Italy, Switzerland, Germany and France.
Two Bulgarian police officers were allegedly involved in the ring.
In other news, Bulgaria sent its first shipment of humanitarian aid to Iraq on Tuesday.
It included food, clothes and medicine.
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 16/04/03;
BTA, BNT, BTV - 15/04/03)
